From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: johnblue <dev@johnblue.local>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] arm: dts: aspeed: ast2600-evb: add mctp-controller to i2c1

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [QEMU development environment only]

The mctp-i2c driver checks for the "mctp-controller" OF property on the
I2C adapter before creating the mctpi2cN netdev (via both probe and the
i2c bus notifier).  Without this property the netdev is never created and
MCTP over I2C is non-functional.

Add the property to bus 1 so that the driver creates mctpi2c1 on boot,
enabling MCTP over I2C for the QEMU AST2600 EVB environment.

Signed-off-by: johnblue <dev@johnblue.local>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/aspeed/aspeed-ast2600-evb.dts | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm/boot/dts/aspeed/aspeed-ast2600-evb.dts b/arch/arm/boot/dts/aspeed/aspeed-ast2600-evb.dts
index 0000000..0000001 100644
--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/aspeed/aspeed-ast2600-evb.dts
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/aspeed/aspeed-ast2600-evb.dts
@@ -215,6 +215,7 @@
 
 &i2c1 {
 	status = "okay";
+	mctp-controller;
 };
 
 &i2c2 {
-- 
2.34.1
